  "backdrop": "city",
  "story": {
    "intro": [
      "Every harvest moon, the rooftops of Lantern City open a single stair to the sky.",
      "Climb it fighting. Nine hands guard the way up; the last wears the moth-silver crown.",
      "You are the Ronin, sworn to no house. Tonight your only house is your own two fists."
    ],
    "levelIntros": [
      "THE TILE GATE: A quick shadow named Tile tests newcomers. Fast, but light. Read the rush.",
      "THE LONG BALCONY: Brass hits like a falling bell. Heavy and slow; punish what he leaves open.",
      "LANTERN ROW: Vesper dances between the lanterns, quick and clever. Corner her and close."
    ],
    "bossIntro": "THE MOTH KING descends, crown dull as old silver. He has held this roof for nine moons. Take it.",
    "victory": [
      "The crown is cold and lighter than it looks. You set it down and let the moon keep it.",
      "Down in the city they will say a masterless fist climbed the sky. Let them. You were only passing through."
    ],
    "defeat": [
      "You fall back down the stair, breath ragged, pride dented. The moon will rise again. So will you.",
      "A hand you could not beat, this time. The rooftops remember every climb. Come back and finish it."
    ]
  },
